🔄 Rotate Your Device 🔄
Inside the Dallas studio of sculptor Dan Lam (@sopopomo), burbling, bubbling and bright works of art appear to move on their own. Commissioned by @Genesis_usa, the artist transformed her distinct style into her first-ever digital art car and NFT inspired by her time in the G70. Lam took inspiration from her time driving the G70, and worked with digital designer Stephen Judge (@stephenthejudge) to bring her vision of the world passing outside the windows to life. #G70artcars #GenesisG70 #G70 #artcars #digitalartcars #NFTs #BorntoMove

node.title: Sculptor Dan Lam Blends the Outside World into Her Genesis G70 Art Car

node.text: For this week’s Milkshake, we invited @noznozawa, founder of San Francisco’s Noz Design. Featuring a vessel from @angusandceleste! \\\ #dmtvmilkshake #designmilktv

node.text: Venezuela-born artist @r.sanguino, who works chiefly in ceramics, makes gorgeous, expressive objects. node.text: We’ve shared our love of @obakki and their purpose-driven designs before, but their Italian glassware collection deserves a post all its own. To start, it's crafted from Swiss borosilicate glass making it durable against cracking and scratching and resistant to extreme temperature changes. But Obakki’s glassware is special beyond that. It's made by third-generation Italian artisan glassblowers and shaped using traditional mouth blowing techniques. The color palette features shades of deep neutral hues that are sure to mix well with the rest of your bar or kitchen. Perhaps most notably, every single piece is one-of-a-kind. \\\ Read more about Obakki's timeless Italian glassware and shop the collection at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: Phase Dance is a weekend home located in a dense forest in Shizuoka, Japan. After visiting the undeveloped site a few times, Takeshi Hirobe Architects took interest in a large orange bark stewartia tree and decided to integrate the tree into their building plans. With the tree being center of the construction area, they designed a crescent-shaped house that wraps around the tree, creating a relationship between the two while allowing the greenery the space it needs to flourish. \\\ Read more about this fantastically designed Japanese #treehouse at the link in bio. 🔗

This month we're feeling Bright + Bold 🔴🟡🔵 and designer Sam Buckley's latest project is inspiring us big time. Buckley is clearly a color aficionado (as evidenced by his two Instagram accounts – @studiosambuckley and @ooooobjectsssss). If you're not convinced, let this apartment do the talking. node.text: @magic_circus_editions, a brand established in 2015 by Marie-Lise Féry, has become known for lighting that plays with shadow and proportion. By rethinking everyday objects, Féry tells stories via airy, playful and magical details. Magic Circus Éditions’ most recent work – the Pop-Up Collection – merges 70s retro aesthetics with contemporary design for imaginative, fun and playful results. The combination of traditional know-how and her imaginative take on historical, everyday objects lends an unexpected and charming quality to her creations. \\\ Read more about the Pop-Up Collection at the link in bio. 🔗

🔄 Rotate Your Device 🔄
Inside the Dallas studio of sculptor Dan Lam (@sopopomo), burbling, bubbling and bright works of art appear to move on their own. Commissioned by @Genesis_usa, the artist transformed her distinct style into her first-ever digital art car and NFT inspired by her time in the G70.
